üìÑ Hospital Network Design

This repository contains the complete network design for a hospital environment with:
- 60 PCs
- 100 CCTV cameras
- 20 Printers
- 20 Wi-Fi Access Points

## Design Highlights
- Floor-wise VLAN segmentation
- One managed core switch
- Mostly unmanaged PoE access switches
- Secure CCTV and Guest Wi-Fi isolation
- Scalable and cost-effective architecture


## Technologies
- VLAN (IEEE 802.1Q)
- PoE Switching
- Inter-VLAN Routing
- Firewall-based Segmentation

Refer to the `/docs` folder for detailed design documentation.


üìò Network-overview


The hospital network uses a star topology with a centralized managed switch acting as
the core/distribution layer.

### Key Principles
- VLAN separation by floor and function
- Minimal management overhead
- High availability for CCTV and clinical systems
- Secure guest access

### Core Components
- Managed L2/L3 Switch
- Firewall / Router
- Unmanaged PoE Access Switches



üß† Vlan-design

| VLAN ID | Name | Purpose |
|-------|------|---------|
| 10 | FLOOR1 | PCs & Printers |
| 20 | FLOOR2 | PCs & Printers |
| 30 | FLOOR3 | PCs & Printers |
| 40 | FLOOR4 | PCs & Printers |
| 50 | CCTV | All Cameras |
| 60 | WIFI_STAFF | Secure Staff Wi-Fi |
| 70 | WIFI_GUEST | Guest Internet Only |
| 99 | MGMT | Network Management |

All VLANs terminate on the core managed switch.



üåê Ip-addressing

| VLAN | Subnet | Gateway |
|----|--------|---------|
| 10 | 192.168.10.0/24 | 192.168.10.1 |
| 20 | 192.168.20.0/24 | 192.168.20.1 |
| 30 | 192.168.30.0/24 | 192.168.30.1 |
| 40 | 192.168.40.0/24 | 192.168.40.1 |
| 50 | 192.168.50.0/24 | 192.168.50.1 |
| 60 | 192.168.60.0/24 | 192.168.60.1 |
| 70 | 192.168.70.0/24 | 192.168.70.1 |
| 99 | 192.168.99.0/24 | 192.168.99.1 |




üîê Security-policy

### Allowed
- Staff Wi-Fi ‚Üí Internal Resources
- PCs ‚Üí Printers
- CCTV ‚Üí NVR
- Management VLAN ‚Üí All devices

### Denied
- Guest Wi-Fi ‚Üí Internal Network
- CCTV ‚Üí Internet
- Guest Wi-Fi ‚Üí Printers/CCTV

Firewall enforces all inter-VLAN access.


‚öôÔ∏è configs/core-switch/vlan-config
vlan 10 name FLOOR1
vlan 20 name FLOOR2
vlan 30 name FLOOR3
vlan 40 name FLOOR4
vlan 50 name CCTV
vlan 60 name WIFI_STAFF
vlan 70 name WIFI_GUEST
vlan 99 name MGMT




üì∂ configs/wifi/ssid-vlan-mapping
SSID: Hospital-Staff
VLAN: 60
Security: WPA2/WPA3-Enterprise

SSID: Hospital-Guest
VLAN: 70
Security: Captive Portal
Client Isolation: Enabled




